 and music. She juxtaposes their interpretations of the situations with the discourse and bureaucracy of international aid organizations, showing the sometimes radical differences between these perspectives. Clark-Kazak not only provides insight into the politics of labelling but offers recommendations for future research, policy, and programs for refugee young people. A remarkable and compelling look at the lives of young refugees, Recounting Migration challenges stereotypes by giving these migrants a long-overdue opportunity to speak for themselves.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aCongolese (Democratic Republic)xPolitical activityzUganda. 0aCongolese (Democratic Republic)zUgandaxSocial conditions. 0aRefugeesxPolitical activityzUganda. 0aRefugeeszUgandaxSocial conditions. 0aYouthxPolitical activityzUganda. 0aYouthzUgandaxSocial conditions. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / International Relations / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978077358608640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780773586086423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780773586086/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles